.<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />- experience restoral for those that can no longer be CS rezzed<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>Um? what do you think a CS rez is? Look. They aren't going to expend that much time and trouble so you can get a 100% rez instead of the 96% rezzes you could have trivially provided for everyone on your raid force already. Exp restoring generally means actually rolling your character back to a backup. That's probably not what you really want to have happen.<br><br>I'm not sure why you make a distinction between a &quot;CS rez&quot; and a &quot;experience restoral&quot;. From your perspective, they're both just recoving the exp you lost dying. Um... Is it really such a big deal to get that 10th of a blue of exp back that you lost? Go kill one mob in WoS. Problem solved! I just don't get this one...<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />- an ongoing dialogue between myself and a member of either SOE CS or SOE Dev about the steps being taken to rectify these issues in a timely fashion<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>In other words, you want to be &quot;special&quot; as though you are the only ones affected by the current server stability problems they've been having.<br><br>Want to be involved? Post *useful* information on the official SOE boards. There's you dialogue right there. What exactly do you think makes you so special that they're going to open up a &quot;special&quot; dialogue just with you, when there are 500,000 other customers who are being affected by the same problem? That's what those boards exist for. You're just going to have to go through that process just like everyone else. You are not a unique snowflake...<br><br><br><br>That's all I really had to say. I just have to laugh when people get all huffy and puffed chest like this. Look. You are just one more of thousands of other people. You aren't special. You may think you are, but from SOE's perspective, you're just one more account. Don't like that? Feel free to go play another game. Guess what? You're just going to be one more account to them too. That's because (drumroll) *that's what you are*! Or do you think that your amazingly valuable $13 a month entitles you to special treatment? Get over yourselves. You're just another face in the crowd...</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
