on EQ's priority are bugs and hacks that affect game integrity and manipuability. As much as I hate to say it this problem falls in the minor catagory.<br><br>Nothing is perfect. Especially when it comes to computers. Chances are this problem will never be solved but if its brought to SOE's attention by enough people it will earn serious attention from SOE.<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />Sending in 200+ petitions a day that say nothing more then &quot;We crashed&quot; does NOT speed up the process, it just keeps people busy that are actually investigating the problem.<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>Exactly. If you want to be a help the petition needs to have as much detail about what was going on at the time of the crash as possible. I probably should have said that in my previous post but I was just posting a simple message and I was a little tired. My mistake.<br><br>Until this problem gets serious attention I would at the very least like an &quot;in-game&quot; acknowledgment of the problem.<br><br>One more time. BE POLITE. When someone DEMANDS something of me they are usually the last person who will get my attention. Think of how many people petition something every day. Demanding service at YOUR CONVENIANCE will usually result you in getting service AFTER everyone else and when the GM gets around to it. Not to mention an empty threat will usually get you no service at all.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
